    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-11-25T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-11-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="500"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.51/11–2547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Chile</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-11-25T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 25, 1947—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>563. For <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_info1">info</gloss> only. Robert Vergara informed Dept that on
                    Nov 18 he had reached agreement with Rogers, <gloss target="#t_Pres1"
                        >Pres</gloss>, For Bondholders Protective Council, on terms settlement of
                        <gloss target="#t_Chil1">Chil</gloss> debt which provide initial interest
                    1–½ percent rising to 3 percent after 1953 and 1 percent amortization.
                    Announcement agreement probably be delayed few weeks since related negotiations
                    with British and Swiss bondholders groups not concluded.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
